Instructions for Kindle Touch
1) Extract kindle-jailbreak-1.15.N-r16256.tar.xz
2) Unzip the contents of the kindle-5.4-jailbreak.zip archive to the root directory of your Kindle
3) Eject & unplug your Kindle
4) Go to [HOME] -> [MENU] > Settings -> [MENU] > Update Your Kindle

Kual + MRPI + USB Networking + SS Hack + Python
1) Put KUAL-KDK-2.0.azw2 somewhere in the documents/ directory tree
2) Copy contents of kual-mrinstaller-1.7.N-r16438.tar.xz to root
3) Copy mrpackages folder to root
4) Eject & unplug Kindle
5) Go to KUAL -> Helpers -> Install MR Packages

Kindle-weather
1) Copy kindle folder to /extensions
2) Ensure .env file in /extensions/kindle has correct vars for user/pass/url
3) Copy the following files into /extensions/kindle/bin
    /linkss/etc/ImageMagick-6/colors.xml
    /linkss/etc/ImageMagick-6/delegates.xml
4) Eject & unplug Kindle
5) Go to KUAL -> Kindle Weather

Done!

Optional USB Networking
On Kindle
1) Put Update_usbnet_0.22.N_install_touch_pw.bin in /mrpackages (if not installed above)
2) Eject & unplug Kindle
3) Go to KUAL -> Helpers -> Install MR Packages
4) Go to KUAL -> USBNewtwork -> * Toggle USBNetwork * 

On PC (Ubuntu)
1) Open your network settings
2) Open "USB Ethernet" settings
3) Open the "IPv4" tab 
4) Set "IPv4 Method" to "Manual"
5) Under "Addresses", set "Address" to 192.168.15.201 and "Netmask" to 255.255.255.0
6) Click "Apply"
7) Restart the connection by disabling it and re-enabling it
8) Run "ssh root@192.168.15.244"

